data.enText: to express great happiness about sth

data.chText: 战争结束，人们终于可以欢欣鼓舞了。
data.enText: When the war ended, people finally had cause to rejoice.

data.chText: 汽车工业对汽车减税感到非常高兴。
data.enText: The motor industry is rejoicing at the cut in car tax.

data.chText: 他们看到儿子恢复了健康，无比高兴。
data.enText: They rejoiced to see their son well again.
to have a name that sounds funny

data.chText: 他有个滑稽的名字叫欧文∙欧文。
data.enText: He rejoiced in the name of Owen Owen.

data.chText: 他有个滑稽的名字叫欧文∙欧文。
data.enText: He rejoiced in the name of Owen Owen.

value.def: If you rejoice, you are very pleased about something and you show it in your behaviour.

example.ex: Garbo plays the Queen, rejoicing in the love she has found with Antonio...
example.tran: 嘉宝饰演王后，陶醉于和安东尼奥的热恋中。

example.ex: A Foreign Ministry statement said that the French government rejoiced at the happy outcome to events...
example.tran: 外交部的声明称法国政府很高兴看到事件得到圆满解决。

example.ex: Party activists in New Hampshire rejoiced that the presidential campaign had finally started.
example.tran: 新罕布什尔州党派激进分子对于总统选举终于启动感到欣喜若狂。

example.ex: There was general rejoicing at the news.
example.tran: 听到这一消息大家普遍感到高兴。

value.def: If you say that a person or thing rejoices in the name of something, you mean that they have a silly or amusing name.

example.ex: ...their tortoise, who rejoiced in the name of Carruthers.
example.tran: 他们养的龟有个搞笑的名字——卡拉瑟斯
